texts directed solely at women, which demanded women’s compliance and exclusive dedication to domesticity. Alongside such examples, Control and Resistance includes texts that offer resistance to the Franco hegemony. If the traditional view of food writing as connected to domesticity viewed such writing as apolitical, this book accordingly foregrounds food discourse as a place where identities were contested.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCookbooksxPolitical aspectszSpainxHistoryy20th century. 0aFood habitsxPolitical aspectszSpainxHistoryy20th century. 0aFood writingxPolitical aspectszSpainxHistoryy20th century. 0aFoodxPolitical aspectszSpainxHistoryy20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCulinary patriotism.  aFood and control.  aFood and resistance.  aFood.  aFranco Spain.  aGastronomic space.  aMonolithic food culture.  aautarky.  abiopolitics.  afood and nationalism.  afood writing.  agender.  ahistory of cookbooks.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP Pilot eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753467740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487534677423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487534677.jpg  a978-3-11-069045-3  UTP Pilot eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-0704